main event: A round white object was observed moving slowly to the west at an altitude of 30-45 degrees, disappearing intermittently for approximately 30-40 minutes.
interesting points: The object appeared larger than an aircraft and emitted bright light with arcs of light flashing outward., The sighting was documented by multiple observers including members of the U.S. Navy., The object was first sighted visually and later observed using a telescope., Weather conditions included 50% cloud cover with 10-12 miles visibility., The sighting occurred at 310 degrees azimuth and 0.45 degrees elevation.
witness description: Randall Brazile SNBM, Gary Smith EM3, Dave Trujillo AN3, Larry Johnson SA, John Perry SA
